The George Brown College offers a Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Certificates and Diplomas (A109) program. This certificate program provides foundational knowledge in mathematics and science for various Health Sciences programs. After completing this program, students can apply to several post-secondary institutions for the following programs: Practical Nursing (S121), Dental Assisting (S113), Orthotics/Prosthetics (S102), Medical Office Administration (S135), and Recreation Management in Gerontology (C152).

Graduates of the A109 program have access to direct pathway options for these programs at George Brown College, but admission is competitive and not guaranteed due to limited seats per intake. This program does not offer a direct pathway to degree programs such as Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BScN). Interested students should apply to the Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Advanced Diplomas and Degrees (A108) for pursuing three-year advanced diplomas or four-year degrees.

Programs and their corresponding codes:
1. Practical Nursing - S121
2. Dental Assisting - S113
3. Orthotic/Prosthetic Technician - S102
4. Office Administration â€“ Health Services - S135
5. Recreation Management in Gerontology - C152
6. Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Advanced Diplomas and Degrees - A108

The A109 Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Certificates and Diplomas program offers a direct pathway to the following programs at George Brown College: Practical Nursing (S121), Dental Assisting, Recreation Management in Gerontology, Fitness and Health Promotion, and Office Administration â€“ Medical. Domestic students should apply through Ontario Colleges, while international students should use the George Brown College Online Application System. Interested individuals can contact the Pathway Advisor via email at preparation@georgebrown.ca or by telephone at 416-415-5000 x2874 for program and pathways information. The Practical Nursing (S121) program has new admission requirements which include an online video interview for all qualified applicants. For more details about college preparation programs, work preparation programs, and other information, visit the respective pages on the George Brown College website. Potential students can sign up for an information session, book a campus tour, or explore the virtual tour to learn more about the college. The Pre-Health Sciences Pathway to Certificates and Diplomas program is taught at the St. James Campus located at 341 King St. E., Toronto, Ontario. Applicants who are former students wishing to return to the program should contact the Program Assistant via email at Christine.Kissoore@georgebrown.ca. For international students, recruitment representatives can be contacted through a virtual meeting or submission of an inquiry on the International Contact Us page.
